  5. Composition strategy

  How app imports and mounts contributors

  - contributorManifest.js explicitly imports contributor factories and calls them with DI dependencies.
  - No autodiscovery, no side-effect registration, no global singleton mutation.
  - Removing one import removes that contributor’s actions from runtime.

  Feature flags and channel/surface gating model

  - Add config/actions.js (/home/merc/Development/current/jskit-ai/apps/jskit-value-app/config/actions.js) for
    exposure and policy toggles only.
  - No legacy/dual-path flags.
  - Suggested config:
  - actions.assistant.enabled
  - actions.assistant.exposedActionIds
  - actions.assistant.blockedActionIds
  - actions.internal.enabled
  - actions.internal.exposedActionIds
  - Surface and channel checks enforced by registry using shared/surfacePaths.js (/home/merc/Development/current/
    jskit-ai/apps/jskit-value-app/shared/surfacePaths.js) and route/request context.

  Dependency injection pattern to avoid circular dependencies

  - Build domain services first in runtime service definitions.
  - Build action contributors from domain services/repositories.
  - Build action registry after contributor creation.
  - Inject only actionExecutor into controllers and assistant orchestration layer.
  - Keep action handlers pure against service dependencies, not controller dependencies.

  API/controller transition from direct service calls to action execution

  - Replace direct service invocations in controllers with actionExecutor.execute(...).
  - Keep transport concerns in controllers: request parsing, status code, headers, stream framing.
  - Move business logic, permission enforcement, audit, idempotency into actions.
  - Applies to adapters/controllers currently used by:
  - auth
  - workspace
  - console
  - settings
  - chat
  - billing
  - assistant
  - projects/deg2rad/history
  - TanStack Query behavior remains valid because client still talks to existing HTTP routes; internals behind
    routes change to action execution.

  Assistant evolution from workspace_rename only

  - Remove hardcoded tool file path usage in workspaceRename.tool.js (/home/merc/Development/current/jskit-ai/apps/
    jskit-value-app/server/modules/ai/lib/tools/workspaceRename.tool.js).
  - Build assistant tool descriptors from action definitions filtered by channel=assistant_tool and surface policy.
  - Keep tool names deterministic and provider-safe, mapped to canonical action IDs internally.
  - No legacy alias retention; workspace_rename is replaced by canonical action tool mapping.

  6. Migration plan (phase-by-phase, no legacy compatibility)

  Phase 0 baseline checks

  - Freeze canonical IDs from actions_map.md (/home/merc/Development/current/jskit-ai/actions_map.md) into shared/
    actionIds.js.
  - Build route-to-action binding map from server/modules/api/routes.js (/home/merc/Development/current/jskit-ai/
    apps/jskit-value-app/server/modules/api/routes.js) and package route modules.
  - Identify every controller method that currently performs business logic side effects outside services.
  - Rollback point: tag action-cutover-phase0; no runtime changes yet.

  Phase 1 scaffolding contracts + registry

  - Create packages/runtime/action-runtime-core.
  - Add action runtime wiring under server/runtime/actions.
  - Register actionRegistry and actionExecutor in runtime services.
  - Rollback point: revert to phase0 tag; no legacy branch retained in code.

  Phase 2 domain contributor implementation

  - Implement contributors for all domains using actions_map.md coverage.
  - Keep handlers using existing domain services first, then refactor internals later if needed.
  - Enforce action-level permission declarations for every action.
  - Rollback point: revert to phase1 tag.

  Phase 3 full API/controller cutover

  - Refactor all API controllers/adapters to call actionExecutor only.
  - Remove direct controller-side business logic that duplicates action pipeline concerns.
  - Keep route schemas for transport validation/docs.
  - Rollback point: revert to phase2 tag and redeploy previous release artifact.

  Phase 4 assistant integration expansion

  - Replace ad-hoc assistant tool wiring in ai.service.js (/home/merc/Development/current/jskit-ai/apps/jskit-value-
    app/server/modules/ai/services/ai.service.js) with action-derived tool catalog.
  - Enforce assistant channel policies through action definitions.
  - Remove workspace_rename-only allowlist model.
  - Rollback point: revert to phase3 tag.

  Phase 5 cleanup and hardening

  - Delete obsolete tool wrappers and controller-side duplicated audit/idempotency logic.
  - Remove dead code paths and stale tests tied to pre-action execution.
  - Update docs and operational runbooks for action metrics/events.
  - Rollback point: revert to phase4 tag.

